WORLD IN BRIEF; 
AFRICA; 
SHEVARDNADZE PLANS TO VISIT 5 NATIONS 
Eduard A. Shevardnadze will visit Africa this month in the first trip by a 
Soviet foreign minister to the continent, the government announced in Moscow. 
Shevardnadze will visit Zambia, Zimbabwe, Mozambique, Angola and Namibia, the 
Foreign Ministry said. He may meet Secretary of State James A. Baker III during 
the March 21 visit to Namibia, formerly South-West Africa, a former German 
colony ruled by South Africa since World War I, the announcement said. 
